      section#code
        h2 Code
        p I consider coding (like writing) as a way to think clearly, and as a means of self-expression.
        p Good code is beautiful. (Not all code needs to be good.)
        p.
          I currently work mostly in Ruby, Python, JavaScript &amp; CoffeeScript;
          previously in C, C++, Common Lisp, Java, SmallTalk, assembly, and (of course) Dylan;
          and smaller projects in Haskell and bash.
          For server work I've used mostly Rails, Django, Sinatra, and Express; MySQL, Postgres, and Redis;
          Apache and nginx; and AWS (and previously DreamHost, SliceHost, and colos).
        p.
          <a href="http://code.osteele.com">GitHub code page</a> lists a few of my current side projects.
          This year these are mostly around music theory and notation.
        p.
          My complete GitHub repository list is <a href="http://github.com/osteele">here</a>.

