        //-     but rather teach them to long for the endless immensity of the sea.
        //-   .small Antoine de Saint-Exupery
        p.
          My favorite developers write code in order to figure out what to say
          as easily as they talk in order to figure out how to code.
          They understand both that a good meeting can prevent a month of wasted coding,
          and that a good line of code can prevent an hour of wasted meeting time.
          They understand that languages, platforms, management styles, and development methodologies
          all trade off between strengths and weaknesses, and are differently appropriate in different contexts.
        p. My favorite co-workers want to point at something and say “we did that!”, and want to have fun getting there.

      section#blog
