        p.
          I published a <a href="http://blog.osteele.com">blog</a> from 2003 to 2008.
        p.
          Popular posts included
          <a href='http://blog.osteele.com/posts/2004/11/ides'>The IDE Divide</a> and
          <a href='http://blog.osteele.com/posts/2007/12/overloading-semicolon'>Overloading Semicolon</a>.
        p.
          Posts that failed to make a splash include
          <a href="http://blog.osteele.com/posts/2004/12/serving-clients">Service Clients</a> (an early attempt to describe AJAX), and
          <a href="http://blog.osteele.com/posts/2003/08/rethinking-mvc">Rethinking MVC</a> (an early attempt to describe <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model_View_ViewModel">MVVM</a>).
        p.
          The illustrations in my <a href='http://blog.osteele.com/posts/2008/05/my-git-workflow'>My Git Workflow</a>
          have been adapted (with permission) and improved many times. You can find better, and interactive, versions elsewhere on the web.

